# Privacy Policy
Last Updated: [04/09/2025]
## 1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how RobloSync (“Bot”) collects, uses, and stores user data within Discord. By using this bot, you agree to the terms outlined below.
## 2. Information Collected
RobloSync collects and stores minimal user data necessary for bot functionality, including:
- Discord User IDs to verify Roblox accounts
- Bound groups and ranks for role management
- Verification status for automated role assignments

## 3. How Data Is Stored & Protected
- Data is stored locally in JSON files on the bot's hosting environment.
- No sensitive personal data (e.g., email addresses, passwords) is collected or stored.
- The bot does not share, sell, or distribute user data to third parties.
- Data may be reset or removed when the bot updates or if required by Discord.

## 4. Data Usage
RobloSync only uses collected data for:
- Managing Discord role assignments
- Binding users to Roblox groups or ranks
- Processing verification requests
- Improving bot functionality

## 5. User Rights & Data Removal
Users may request removal of their stored data by contacting the bot owner. Upon request, the bot owner will:
- Delete stored user verification data
- Remove bound roles from Discord servers
- Stop processing verification requests for the user

## 6. Changes to Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Continued use of the bot after updates indicates agreement with any changes.
## 7. Contact & Support
For inquiries, data requests, or support, please contact [@.exonontom].
